sequenceDiagram
    actor User as ML Engineer
    participant API as Kubernetes API
    participant Trainer as trainer<br/>(Trainer v2)
    participant JobSet as JobSet Controller
    participant Pods as Distributed Training Pods<br/>(multi-node)
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry
    participant KServe as KServe
    participant LLMService as LLMInferenceService

    User->>API: 1. Create TrainJob CR<br/>(LLM fine-tuning config)
    API->>Trainer: 2. Reconcile TrainJob

    Note over Trainer,JobSet: Distributed Pod Setup
    Trainer->>JobSet: 3. Create JobSet<br/>(coordinated pod group)
    JobSet->>Pods: 4. Create distributed training pods<br/>(master + workers)

    Note over Pods,S3: Model & Data Loading
    Pods->>HF: 5a. Download base LLM<br/>(e.g., Llama-2-7B)
    Pods->>S3: 5b. Load training dataset

    Note over Pods: Distributed Training
    Pods->>Pods: 6. Initialize DeepSpeed/Megatron<br/>(distributed training framework)
    Pods->>Pods: 7. Multi-node LLM fine-tuning<br/>(parameter sharding, gradient sync)

    Note over Pods,MLflow: Monitoring & Checkpointing
    loop Every N steps
        Pods->>MLflow: 8a. Log loss, perplexity, LR
        Pods->>S3: 8b. Save checkpoints
    end

    Note over Pods,ModelReg: Model Registration
    Pods->>S3: 9a. Save final fine-tuned model
    Trainer->>ModelReg: 9b. Register model<br/>(version, base model, dataset)

    Note over User,LLMService: Deployment
    User->>API: 10a. Create LLMInferenceService CR
    API->>KServe: 10b. Deploy LLM with vLLM runtime
    KServe->>S3: 10c. Load fine-tuned model
    KServe->>LLMService: 10d. Serve LLM inference endpoint

    Note over User,LLMService: Ready for Inference
    User->>LLMService: 11. Send prompts to fine-tuned LLM
    LLMService->>User: 12. Return generated text
